    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="233" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName>Mr.
                                Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1418.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 22, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> There are no events of sufficient
                            importance to mention since the last weekly summary, that are not
                            clearly stated in the official bulletin of the War Department published
                            in the Chronicle newspaper, the files of which are now regularly
                            forwarded to all of our legations. The Stonewall at last advices was at
                            Havana, and energetic measures have been adopted with a view to her
                            capture or destruction.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>[Same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis,</hi> to all our principal
                                ministers in Europe.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
